cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on studying the impact of full-duplex communications on cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a novel duplexing scheme and derives the conditions for rate gains, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with the performance evaluation of communication systems in cellular networks. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new system design for cellular networks, which involves control and optimization aspects. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of full-duplex communications on the uplink and downlink rates, which are relevant to multimedia applications.
